<subSubSection box="[316,1550,1767,1805]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[164,1550,1708,1805]" box="[316,1550,1767,1805]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">
Derivation: Gr. 
<emphasis box="[568,654,1768,1795]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Stems</emphasis>
= narrow; 
<emphasis box="[840,899,1777,1795]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">oura</emphasis>
= tail. Refers to the narrow gonocoxites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="295" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[166,1563,1850,2172]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">
Description: Agrees very closely with the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo." authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Ricardo" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1206,1336,1850,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1231,1850,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1257,1336,1850,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except for the following points:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[166,1563,1850,2172]" box="[315,1404,1932,1969]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Head: A11 antennal segments orange. Mystacal bristles yellow-white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[166,1563,1850,2172]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">
Thorax: 4, supra-alar bristles. Legs: femora yellow-brown ventrally and distally on dorsal aspects. Wings: 
<quantity box="[625,817,2015,2049]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="8.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" unit="mm" value="88.0" valueMax="93.0" valueMin="83.0">83-93 mm</quantity>
long; 
<quantity box="[922,1111,2022,2048]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.7">2,7—3,2 mm</quantity>
wide (in the northern Cape 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo." authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Ricardo" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[166,244,2055,2082]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[166,244,2055,2082]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally a slightly larger species). Cell 
<emphasis box="[921,965,2059,2090]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">cup</emphasis>
close to wing margin. Abdomen: d‘ genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[764,928,2095,2131]" captionStart="Figs 22-24" captionStartId="13.[315,370,1636,1667]" captionTargetBox="[350,1689,428,1596]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 22-24. Daspletis stenoura spec. nov. paratype male genitalia. 22. Lateral. 23. Ventral. 2 4.Dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4030772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4030772/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Figs 22-24</figureCitation>
..
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[166,1563,1850,2172]" box="[314,1169,2136,2172]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Variation: Only minor sexual dimorphism as in hirtus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
