<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[314,1707,1986,2139]" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">
Remarks: A species very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo." authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Ricardo" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1049,1182,1986,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[1049,1077,1986,2014]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1104,1182,1986,2014]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but male genitalia with narrow fused gonocoxites quite easily distinguished from those of 
<emphasis box="[1240,1317,2028,2056]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">hiríus</emphasis>
. Females are difficult to separate but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londt" authorityYear="1983" box="[519,629,2075,2097]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspietis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoura">
<emphasis box="[519,629,2075,2097]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">stenoura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bristles, especially those of the legs, somewhat yellower than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo." authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Ricardo" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[314,391,2112,2139]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[314,391,2112,2139]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="296">hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
